fields.title: Jabal al Thawr
fields.description: Begin your journey at the majestic Jabal al Thawr, an awe-inspiring mountain that holds a special place in Islamic history.

fields.title: Mina
fields.description: Visit the holy valley of Mina, where pilgrims participate in symbolic rituals during Hajj.

fields.title: Jamarat
fields.description: Reflect at the Jamarat, the symbolic pillars where pilgrims cast stones as part of the Hajj rituals.

fields.title: Arafat
fields.description: Experience the sacred plains of Arafat, where the most important Hajj ritual takes place.

fields.title: Jabal ar Rahmah
fields.description: Stand where Prophet Muhammad (peace be upon him) delivered his Farewell Sermon.

fields.title: Muzdalifah
fields.description: Explore the serene Muzdalifah, a site where pilgrims spend a night during Hajj.

fields.title: Waadi Muhassar
fields.description: Discover Waadi Muhassar, a place of historical and spiritual significance.

fields.title: Masjid Nimrah
fields.description: Visit Masjid Nimrah, where the Prophet Muhammad (peace be upon him) delivered his Farewell Sermon during his final pilgrimage.

fields.title: Masjid Aisha
fields.description: Explore Masjid Aisha, a site of importance during the Hajj journey.

fields.title: Masjid-Al-Jinn
fields.description: Delve into the mysteries of Masjid al-Jin, a mosque mentioned in Islamic tradition.

fields.title: Jabal al-Hira
fields.description: The cave where the Prophet Muhammad (peace be upon him) received the first revelation.

fields.title: Jannatul Mualla
fields.description: Pay your respects at Jannatul Mualla, the sacred cemetery in Makkah.

fields.title: Al Masjid Al Nabawi (The Prophet's Mosque)
fields.description: Begin your tour with a visit to the magnificent Al Masjid Al Nabawi, one of the largest mosques in the world. Enter through the King Fahad Gate No. 334 and immerse yourself in the tranquility of this sacred site.

fields.title: Al-Baqi'
fields.description: Continue to Al-Baqi', the famous cemetery adjacent to the mosque, which serves as the final resting place of many family members of the Prophet (PBUH) and his companions.

fields.title: Al Manakhah Square
fields.description: Discover Al Manakhah Square, where you can explore the surrounding area including Al Ghamama Mosque and the start of the path of AL Sunnah.

fields.title: Al Salam Gate
fields.description: Proceed to the Al Salam Gate and take in the view of the Saqeefah Bani Saedah, a notable historical site.

fields.title: Uhud Battlefield
fields.description: Visit the Uhud Battlefield, where the famous battle took place. Pay your respects at the Mount Uhud and the Graveyard of Martyrs.

fields.title: Al-Noor Mall
fields.description: After a morning of historical exploration, enjoy some leisure time at Al-Noor Mall with various dining and shopping options.

fields.title: Sultana Road
fields.description: Drive along Sultana Road, where you can see the bustling city life with a mix of modernity and tradition.

fields.title: Al Qiblatayn Mosque
fields.description: Witness the Al Qiblatayn Mosque, famous for being the site where the Qibla was changed from Jerusalem to Mecca.

fields.title: The Trench Battlefield (Battle of the Trench)
fields.description: Visit the site of the Battle of the Trench, an important event in Islamic history.

fields.title: Masjid Quba
fields.description: Make a stop at Masjid Quba, the first mosque in Islamic history, at the end of the path of AL Sunnah.

fields.title: Al Hijaz Railway Station
fields.description: Explore the historic Al Hijaz Railway Station and the adjacent Dar Al Qalam Museum.

fields.title: Quba Boulevard
fields.description: Conclude your tour with a drive along Quba Boulevard, which leads back into the city center.
